article.headline: Texas-San Antonio 73, Cent. Arkansas 60
article.story: CONWAY, Ark. -- Sei Paye scored 15 points and Jeromie Hill had 13 points and 11 rebounds Wednesday night to help Texas-San Antonio defeat Central Arkansas 73-60. Igor Nujic and Kannon Burrage also scored 13 points for UTSA, and Michael Hale III finished with 10 as all five starters scored in double figures for the Roadrunners (17-13, 9-6 Southland). Jarvis Garner led the Bears (8-20, 3-12) with 12 points. LaQuentin Miles and Mark Rutledge had 10 points each for Central Arkansas. The Roadrunners finished with a 50-31 rebounding advantage. Paye grabbed eight rebounds and Burrage seven.
